SIMPLE: malkin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Malkin
<hw>Mal"kin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>Maud</ets>, the proper name. Cf. <er>Grimalkin</er>.]</ety>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>maukin</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Originally, a kitchenmaid; a slattern.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A mop made of clouts, used by the kitchen
servant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A scarecrow.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>A mop or sponge attached to a
jointed staff for swabbing out a cannon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mall</ent>⟦br⟧
